annotationA: Proteasome subunit beta type; Threonine-type endopeptidase activity; endopeptidase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: cellular response to DNA damage stimulus; proteasome-mediated ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process
annotationB: Ubiquitin specific protease 14 (Usp14) is a deubiquitinase that associates with the 19S component of the proteasome in a reversible manner. Usp14 functions include ubiquitin chain disassemblance for mono-ubiquitin recycling, control of protein degradation by the proteasome and regulation of proteasome subtrate interactions; Belongs to the peptidase C19 family
